This 19-year-old man reported the onset of nonthunderclap headaches 4 months ago.
This can last for 4 hours at a time. They are severe and alleviated by lying down with
photophobia and phonophobia and some dizziness with nausea. He went for an MRI which
was apparently normal. No fever, chills, sweats, history of cancer, or other vision loss,
diplopia, dysphagia, dysphonia, sensorimotor disturbance in the extremities. No Valsalva
Advil or Tylenol do not particularly help. He previously tried sumatriptan/naproxen 85/500
mg which has not been very affective. These are severe for about 2-5 days in a month.
